  <title>Weeks 4 Assignment</title>
  <p><ol>
    <li>
      <p>
        Calculate the following limits. (12)
      </p>
      <p><ol>
        <li><me>
          \lim_{x \rightarrow 1} \frac{x^2 - 1}{x^2 + x - 2}
        </me></li>
        <li><me>
          \lim_{x \rightarrow 1} \frac{x^2 + 2x + 1}{x^2 + 5x + 6}
        </me></li>
        <li><me>
          \lim_{x \rightarrow 1} \frac{x^2 - 1}{x^2 - 2x + 1}
        </me></li>
        <li><me>
          \lim_{x \rightarrow 0} \frac{\tan^2 x + \sin^2 x}{x^2}
        </me></li>
      </ol></p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        For each of the following functions, find a value of <m>a</m>
        that makes the function continuous or demonstrate that no
        value of <m>a</m> is possible. (12) 
      </p>
      <p><ol>
        <li><me>
          f(x) = \left\{ \begin{matrix}
            x^2 - 4 \amp x \lt 0 \\
            x^3 + a \amp x \geq 0 
          \end{matrix} \right.
        </me></li>
        <li><me>
          f(x) = \left\{ \begin{matrix}
            \ln (x + a) \amp x \geq 0 \\
            \sqrt{-x} \amp x \lt 0
          \end{matrix} \right.
        </me></li>
        <li><me>
          f(x) = \left\{ \begin{matrix}
            (x + 2)^2  \amp |x| \lt 4 \\
            ax^2 \amp |x| \geq 4
          \end{matrix} \right.
        </me></li>
      </ol></p>
    </li>
  </ol></p>
